guide~
Travelers throughout the land have long used herbs as a vital tool,
whether for medicinal purposes or for more inherent magical qualities. 
Painstaking research has shown that there are a variety of sources to be
found in several different regions throughout Krynn.  The following
information, based upon the field reports of our fellow scholar
Adrastos, lists the currently known species of herbal variants.  
 
SOLAMNIA
Just east of Palanthas lies a small shop run by a woman known as Uronia.
Within, one may find select from a Red herb known to induce a state of
battle frenzy, a Purple herb granting exceptional speed, a Pinkish herb
that likewise bestows great strength, and a Yellow herb favored by mages;
often used to improve their powers of observation.
 
NERAKA
The dragonarmies and servants of the Dark Queen often make use of herbal
lore to increase their abilities, and several vendors may be found
throughout the capital city. Herbs of recall are used to transport troops
to a specified location, but often exact a demanding toll on the health
of the user; these may be found in any of the city's Quarters.

Similarly, several of the Quarters have attempted to develop their own
versions of these herbs, naming them after their respective Quarters.
However, the process has proved to be even more unstable; while many
carry the same health risk, instead of sending the user to a central
destination, the magic seems to teleport the user to a random location!
Of these ill-conceived mixtures, the Red Quarters herb seems to be the
only partial success in that while the teleport is still random, no loss
of health has been shown to occur.

Servants of the Queen also favor what have come to be known as Herbs of
Power, and may be found in most Quarters of the city. These herbs serve to
invigorate the user; making them less weary and augmenting their strength.
Herbalists in the Black and White Quarters of the city have been especially
successful with this recipe, and their versions of the herb have been known
to augment speed as well.

As a final note - Beware of Merchants claiming to offer Healing herbs! Many
scholars have reported purchasing these remedies in good faith, only to
discover that they have no effect! In addition, many have also reported
their food supply poisoned, perhaps tainted by some chemical reaction while
being stored in close proximity.
~
