ABASINIA AND OTHERS
Dedicated researchers of herb lore may find themselves traveling far and
wide to complete their studies; often finding themselves in strange and
disreputable places, searching for that one elusive gem of knowledge...
 
One such example lies in the crime-ridden city of Port O' Call. Infamous
for it's reputation as a home to pirates, smugglers, and thieves it
nonetheless holds a few precious secrets. One of these is a vendor known
as Mareen. Specializing in imported items of questionable origin, she
offers the sale of a Brown herb highly prized by many spellcasters
for its ability to enhance the intellect; enabling them to better
attune themselves to magical energies.
 
While many consider Kender to be little more than a nuisance, surprisingly
Kendermore itself is home to some of the most skilled herbalists on Krynn.
One such kender herbalist has discovered a Red herb unparalleled in it's
vision-enhancing capabilities. Likewise, his White herbs' medicinal uses
in both healing and refreshing rival that of many clerics! Indeed, many
priests traveling abroad consider the Yellow herb offered by the kender
to be sacred in many religions; those who partake of it have reported
feelings of protection and divine favor. The Green herb is also useful for
traveling through dangerous lands, warding the user against evil and
making them extremely difficult to be seen.
 
Finally, those traveling through the wasteland known as the Plains of Dust
would do well to seek out a Wanderer who makes his home there. Having spent
many years in the harsh climate, he has discovered a Root essential to
desert survival. While it comes at a price, this root is known to have
many beneficial qualities; not only invigorating the user, but also giving
them increased strength to weather the harsh conditions as well as enabling
them to travel more quickly.
~
