Here a large intersection connects the separate wings of the Hall. 
Bookshelves continue to line a vast circular chamber, surrounding a common
area lined with tables where members may study in peace.  In the center of
the room stands a finely crafted fountain adorned with a statue of Gilean. 
A richly embroidered carpet stretches down each of the four major hallways. 
Looking at the delicate stitchwork, you realize that what seemed at first to
be an intricate design is actually tiny lettering; the names of all of the
